# Foundational Data Processing and Descriptor Calculation

This folder contains code and notebooks for handling chemical crystal data and extracting molecular descriptors. The scripts demonstrate data loading, cleaning, normalization, and calculation of 2D/3D molecular descriptors along with charge and chemical feature descriptors.

Key content:
- Data preprocessing scripts for refinement and normalization.
- Descriptor calculators (2D, 3D, charge) to generate feature sets from crystal molecular structures.
- Summary scripts for aggregating descriptor data and statistical analysis.

These form the backbone for downstream cheminformatics analyses and machine learning modeling.

## Usage

Run the scripts/notebooks sequentially for extracting and preparing descriptor datasets. Required inputs are crystal reference codes and structure files as CSV or CSD format.

## Dependencies

- Python 3.x
- pandas
- numpy
- rdkit
- matplotlib (for visualization)
- CCDC Python API (for reading crystal data)
